<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40100d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40100d">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40100d"> 100(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Lupus made / answer</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">O dear my son, they said to the wolf, &lsquo;avoid the sheep lest haply the dust they raise in flight may do thee a damage;&rsquo; but Lupus <font color="green">[the wolf]</font> made answer; &lsquo;Verily, their dust is a powder good for the eyes.&rsquo; <small> Richard F. Burton, trans. <a name="RFBS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RFBS"><cite title="source">Supplemental Nights to the Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night with Notes Anthropological and Explanatory</cite></a> (n.d.) xvi.29</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
